["Base class for exceptions on the project and unhandled errors "]}, {"name": "core_https.exceptions.AuthorizationException", "bases": ["InternalServerError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception caused for authentication (401, 403) issues "]}, {"name": "core_https.exceptions.ServiceException", "bases": ["InternalServerError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception caused for handled errors within the service "]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "core_https", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "core_https.StatusInfo", "bases": ["StrEnum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "core_https.StatusInfo.SUCCESS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "core_https.StatusInfo.ERROR", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "core_https.StatusInfo.FAILURE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["StatusInfo is a literal representation of the response depending on\nthe status_code received...\n\n  * success: is for HTTP statuses 1XX, 2XX and 3XX.\n  * error: is for HTTP statuses from 400 to 499.\n  * fail: is for HTTP statuses from 500 to 599."]}], "exports": [{"name": "core_https.StrEnum", "xref": {"fqname": "enum.StrEnum", "project": null}}, {"name": "core_https.StrEnum", "xref": {"fqname": "core_https.utils.StrEnum", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "core_https.decorators", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "core_https.decorators.wrapp_response", "xref": {"fqname": "core_https.decorators.response_wrapper.wrapp_response", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "core_https.decorators.response_wrapper", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "core_https.decorators.response_wrapper.wrapp_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fnc", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "...", "xref": null, "params": null}, {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "HTTPStatus", "xref": {"fqname": "core_https.utils.HTTPStatus", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This decorator provides a generic mechanism to return the response payload\nfor the endpoints in the same format. This way each router or controller does not\nneed to take care of it. It returns the response into the below format...\n\nResponse payload:\n    {\n        \"code\": 2XX | 4XX | 5XX,\n        \"status\": \"success\" | \"error\" | \"failure\",\n        \"result\": ...\n        \"error\": ...,\n    }\n\nWhere:\n    code:\n        - 2XX -> For success responses.\n        - 4XX -> For service-managed errors.\n        - 5XX -> For unmanaged or internal server errors.\n\n    status:\n        Contains the text: \"success\", \"failure\", or \"error\". Where \"failure\" is for HTTP status\n        response values from 500 to 599, \"error\" is for statuses from 400 to 499, and \"success\" is\n        for everything else (e.g. 1XX, 2XX and 3XX responses).\n\n    result:\n        Contains the result.\n\n    error:\n        Only used for \"failure\" and \"error\" statuses, and it contains the error information."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "core_https.utils", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "core_https.utils.HTTPStatus", "bases": ["Enum"], "methods": [{"name": "core_https.utils.HTTPStatus.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "code", "type": null, "default": null}, {"nam